<paragraph id="8BC736DA7A54FFD2FFCBFDD1FDC9FD2D" blockId="23.[96,686,528,647]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Known as the 
<emphasis id="B90CEAC87A54FFD2FEA3FDD3FDC8FD83" box="[264,522,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Coastal Peacock Spider</emphasis>
, this spider is common on plants in coastal sand dunes in the vicinity of Perth. Males have a fringe comprised of long, bicoloured setae around the fan.
</paragraph>
